{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"isHeader":true,"content":"Preparation","step":0},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Preheat oven to 200°C and line a large baking tray with baking paper. Place a long sheet of baking paper (130 cm) on a work surface.","step":1},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place butter in mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min 30 sec\/80°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","step":2},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Place parsley and chilli in mixing bowl then chop <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <b>2 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","step":3},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add spinach, cream cheese, lemon juice and salt then, with aid of spatula, mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","step":4},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Add pecans and salmon then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","step":5},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Working as quickly as possible to avoid pastry drying out, lay 3 sheets filo pastry end-to-end on long sheet of baking paper then brush generously with reserved melted butter. Lay another 3 sheets filo pastry on top and brush with more melted butter. Repeat for 2 more layers, brushing generously with melted butter after each layer.","step":6},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Evenly distribute salmon mixture along one long side of pastry sheets forming a long log. Brush remaining exposed pastry with melted butter, then carefully roll pastry into a long sausage shape to encase filling. Coil pastry around itself into a spiral, brushing with extra melted butter as needed, then transfer to prepared tray.","step":7},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Patch up any breaks in pastry with small pieces of filo and melted butter.","step":8},{"isHeader":false,"content":"Bake for 30-40 minutes (200°C) until pastry is golden and crispy. Cut in wedges and serve hot.","step":9}],"usefulItems":"baking paper, pastry brush, large baking tray, oven","